==International career== Hernandez made his international debut for [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] on 13 October 2018, starting in the [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League D]] match against [[Armenia national football team|Armenia]] before coming off in the 85th minute for [[Ethan Britto]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/season=2019/matches/round=2000959/match=2024126/index.html |title=UEFA Nations League – Armenia v Gibraltar |website=UEFA.com |publisher=[[UEFA|Union of European Football Associations]] |date=13 October 2018 |access-date=13 October 2018}}</ref> The match finished as a 1–0 away win for Gibraltar, their first ever competitive victory.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45851081 |title=Gibraltar win competitive match for first time, beating Armenia 1–0 |website=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation |date=13 October 2018 |access-date=14 October 2018}}</ref> At the November match against [[Macedonia national football team|Macedonia]] on the road, he impressed the home crowed with his dribbling skills.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://macedonianfootball.com/uefa-nations-league-macedonia-gibraltar-40/ |title=UEFA Nations League: Macedonia – Gibraltar 4:0 (Video) |website=[[MacedonianFootball]] |publisher=MacedonianFootball |date=19 November 2018 |access-date=20 November 2018}}</ref>
==Personal life== Hernandez's older brother [[Anthony Hernandez (footballer)|Anthony]] is also a footballer, playing with [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.|Lincoln Red Imps]] and the Gibraltar national team.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://gibraltarunitedfc.wordpress.com/2016/10/23/gibaltar-united-football-club-vs-st-josephs-football-club/ |title=Gibaltar United Football Club vs St Joseph's Football Club |publisher=[[Gibraltar United F.C.]] |date=23 October 2016 |access-date=13 October 2018 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181013163414/https://gibraltarunitedfc.wordpress.com/2016/10/23/gibaltar-united-football-club-vs-st-josephs-football-club/ |archive-date=13 October 2018}}</ref>
