{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Indian Gymkhana Cricket Club Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Osterley]], [[London]] | establishment = 1916 | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = | club1 = | date = 2 September | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/670.html Ground profile }}
'''Indian Gymkhana Cricket Club Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Osterley]], [[London]] (formerly [[Middlesex]]). which was founded in 1916. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1932, when Indian Gymkhana played the touring [[India national cricket team|Indians]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/670.html Other matches played on Indian Gymkhana Cricket Club Ground]</ref> The ground has also held [[Middlesex County Cricket Club|Middlesex Second XI]] fixtures, the first of which came in the 1935 [[Minor Counties Championship]] when the Middlesex Second XI played the [[Glamorgan County Cricket Club|Glamorgan Second XI]]. From 1935 to 1936, the ground hosted four Minor Counties Championship matches, the last of which saw the Middlesex Second XI play [[Cornwall County Cricket Club|Cornwall]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/670_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Indian Gymkhana Cricket Club Ground]</ref>
In 1986, the ground held a single [[Women's One Day International cricket|Women's One Day International]] between [[England women's cricket team|England women]] and [[India women's cricket team|India women]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/670_wo.html Women's One-Day International Matches played on Indian Gymkhana Cricket Club Ground]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, the ground is the home venue of Indian Gymkhana Cricket Club.<ref>[http://www.indiangymkhanaclub.co.uk/ Indian Gymkhana Cricket Club]</ref> The ground also has [[field hockey|hockey]] and [[association football|football]] playing facilities hosting the [[Indian Gymkhana F.C.]]
