{{use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} {{Portuguese name|Da Silva|Inchude}} {{Infobox athlete | name =Jessica Inchude | image = | caption = | fullname = | nicknames = | nationality = | strokes = | club = | collegeteam = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|3|25|df=yes}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | height = | sport = [[Track and field|Athletics]] | weight = | country =Guinea-Bissau | medaltemplates = | show-medals = | updated = }}
'''Jessica da Silva Inchude''' (born 25 March 1996) is a [[Bissau-Guinea]]n [[shot put]]ter and [[discus throw]]er.
At the 2016 African Championships she finished fourth in the [[2016 African Championships in Athletics – Women's shot put|shot put]] and ninth in the [[2016 African Championships in Athletics – Women's discus throw|discus throw]]. At the [[Athletics at the 2017 Islamic Solidarity Games – Results|2017 Islamic Solidarity Games]] she won the gold medal in the discus and finished fourth in the shot put.
She competed in the [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Women's shot put|women's shot put]] event at the [[2016 Summer Olympics]], where she finished 36th with a distance of 15.15 metres. She did not advance to the final.<ref name="Bio">{{cite web|url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/jessica-inchude |title=Jessica Inchude |accessdate=13 August 2016 |work=Rio 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160806065925/https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/jessica-inchude |archivedate= 6 August 2016 |df= }}</ref> She also competed at the [[2017 World Championships in Athletics – Women's shot put|2017 World Championships]] without reaching the final.<ref>{{iaaf name|293965}}</ref>
